<h1>Leathercraft</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Describe, name, or explain the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>Sources or leather
<li>Curing and tanning of leather
<li>Kinds of dyeing, staining and polishing, and cleaning material used in leatherwork.</ol><p>

<li>Do the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>Identify at least five (5) different types of leather.
<li>Explain how to select and buy leather.
<li>Tell what kind of leather is best for each type of leatherwork such as: tooled and stamped or embossed articles like moccasins, wallet, shoes, bags, novelties, etc.</ol><p>

<li>Tell the proper use and care of leatherwork tools and equipment.<p>

<li>Design patterns for at least three (3) different articles: wallet, leather case, shoes, belt, etc.<p>

<li>Demonstrate at least three (3) types of lacing, and at least three (3) methods of braiding.<p>

<li>Make at least three (3) pieces of hand-carved and laced articles: leather cases, purses, billfold, portfolios, handbags, belts, etc.</ol>


</span><p>
